cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification (ReID), which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new formulation for distribution alignment, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new mechanism for camera alignment, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves domain adaptation and incremental learning, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of distribution inconsistency, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
